## Summary of Changes from v0.0.1

### What Changed

| Aspect | v0.0.1 | v0.0.2 |
|--------|--------|--------|
| Operator key management | Individual secp256k1 keys, manually managed | Safe{Wallet} smart account with N owners and configurable threshold |
| M-of-N enforcement | Off-chain, in fleet server Python code | On-chain, in Safe smart contract. Trustless and auditable. |
| Policy enforcement | Server-side only (Python + Redis) | Dual: server-side (Python) + on-chain (Safe Guard contract) |
| Remote signing | Not supported. QR/NFC only. | Supported. Safe collects signatures asynchronously. ERC-4337 UserOps. |
| Gas costs | Unaddressed. Operators need ETH. | Paymaster-sponsored. Fleet treasury or sponsor covers gas. |
| Fleet server trust | Trusted key holder with secp256k1 key | Constrained Safe Module. Executes within Guard rules. Revocable. |
| Audit trail | Centralized server database. Tamperable. | On-chain. Every Safe transaction is a permanent, public record. |
| Key rotation | Manual ERC-8004 update via Privy tx | Safe owner swap tx. Approved by remaining owners. Address unchanged. |
| Single server key risk | Key compromise = full server rotation | Module is permissioned, not key-based. Revoke + deploy new one. |

### What Didn't Change

- ATECC608B hardware identity (P-256, non-extractable)
- ERC-8128 per-request HTTP authentication
- ERC-8004 on-chain agent registry
- Privy wallet for financial identity
- Firmware attestation flow
- Action tier classification (Tier 0-3)
- x402 payment integration
- Core 2-of-3 signing requirement

---

## 1. Abstract

This protocol extends v0.0.1 by replacing the operator layer with a
Safe{Wallet} smart account and converting the fleet policy server from a
trusted key holder into a constrained Safe Module. This moves M-of-N operator
authorization, policy enforcement, and audit logging on-chain, eliminating
several trust assumptions from the previous version.

The 2-of-3 structure remains: Robot (ATECC608B) + Server (Safe Module) +
Operator (Safe Owners). But "Operator" is now a programmable, multi-party,
on-chain governance layer with battle-tested smart contracts securing over
$60B in assets.

