## 6. Action Tiers (Updated)

| Tier | Signer | Mechanism | Examples |
|------|--------|-----------|----------|
| Tier 0: Baseline | Robot ECC608 + Safe Module (auto) | Module calls `execTransactionFromModule`. Guard validates tier ≤ 1. | Telemetry, heartbeat |
| Tier 1: Elevated | Robot ECC608 + Safe Module (rate-limited) | Same as Tier 0 but Guard enforces spending cap. | x402 micropayments |
| Tier 2: Privileged | Robot ECC608 + Safe Owners (M-of-N) | Safe owners propose and sign. Guard allows any tier for owners. | Firmware update, autonomous mode |
| Tier 3: Admin | Safe Owners (M-of-N) | Safe owners propose and sign. No robot involved. | Revoke device, update policy |

### Tier 2 Flow (with Safe)

```
1.  Robot encounters privileged action (e.g., firmware update)
2.  Robot signs ActionRequest with ECC608
3.  Fleet server receives request, classifies as Tier 2
4.  Server proposes Safe transaction via Safe Transaction Service API
    POST https://safe-transaction-base.safe.global/
      api/v1/safes/{safe}/multisig-transactions/
5.  Safe owners receive notification (mobile app, email, push)
6.  Owners review action details in Safe{Wallet} UI or mobile app
7.  Owners sign from anywhere (Ledger, mobile, passkeys)
8.  Once threshold met (e.g., 2-of-3), Safe executes transaction
9.  Guard validates the action
10. Fleet server receives confirmation, forwards to robot
11. Robot proceeds with firmware update
```

### Tier 3 Flow (Admin without Robot)

```
1. Any Safe owner proposes admin action (e.g., revoke robot)
2. Other owners cosign via Safe{Wallet} UI
3. Guard validates (if applicable)
4. Safe executes: update ERC-8004 registry, quarantine in Guard
```

