## 7. ERC-4337 Integration

### 7.1 Gasless Operator Signing

Safe's ERC-4337 integration enables operators to approve fleet actions
without holding ETH:

```
1. Operator signs a UserOperation (off-chain, no gas)
2. UserOperation is sent to a Bundler
3. Bundler submits to EntryPoint contract
4. Paymaster (fleet treasury) pays gas on behalf of the operator
5. Safe validates signatures and executes
```

### 7.2 Paymaster Configuration

```json
{
  "paymaster": "0xFleetPaymaster",
  "funding_source": "fleet_treasury",
  "sponsored_actions": [
    "device_revocation",
    "firmware_approval",
    "policy_change",
    "emergency_stop",
    "owner_rotation"
  ],
  "max_gas_per_operation": "500000",
  "daily_gas_budget": "10000000"
}
```

### 7.3 Passkey Support

Safe supports passkeys (WebAuthn) as signer authentication. Field technicians
can approve Tier 2 actions using biometrics on their phone — no private key
management, no seed phrases, no hardware wallet required.

