## 9. Recovery Scenarios (Updated)

| Scenario | Recovery Pair | Procedure | Improvement over v0.0.1 |
|----------|--------------|-----------|------------------------|
| Robot stolen | Safe owners | Propose revocation tx in Safe. 2-of-3 approve. Guard quarantines. | Async remote approval instead of physical presence. |
| Firmware compromised | Server + Safe owners | Server auto-quarantines (attestation mismatch). Owners approve re-flash via Safe. | Guard enforces quarantine on-chain even if server is bypassed. |
| Fleet server compromised | Safe owners | Owners revoke module via Safe tx. Deploy new module. No key rotation. | Module revocation is atomic and on-chain. No key to steal. |
| Fleet server down | Safe owners direct | Owners submit Tier 2/3 txs directly via Safe UI. Tier 0/1 paused. | Safe operates independently of server. |
| Operator compromised | Other Safe owners | `swapOwner` tx to remove compromised owner. Threshold enforced. | Atomic on-chain swap. Safe address unchanged. |
| Multiple operators compromised | Remaining owners + social recovery | Safe recovery module with trusted guardians. Time-locked recovery. | Built-in Safe recovery infrastructure. |

