## 11. Security Properties (Updated)

### New Guarantees in v0.0.2

| Property | Mechanism |
|----------|-----------|
| On-chain M-of-N | Safe contract enforces threshold. Not software, not server code. Trustless. |
| On-chain policy backstop | Guard contract validates actions independently of server. Server compromise limited. |
| Remote multi-party approval | Safe collects signatures asynchronously. Operators in different locations/timezones. |
| Gasless operations | ERC-4337 + Paymaster. Operators don't need ETH. Lowers barrier. |
| Atomic key rotation | Safe `swapOwner` is a single on-chain tx. No ERC-8004 update needed. |
| Permanent audit trail | Every Safe tx is on-chain. Immutable record. |
| Module revocability | Compromised server module disabled in one Safe tx. No key material to steal. |

### Updated Threat Model

| Threat | v0.0.1 Impact | v0.0.2 Impact |
|--------|--------------|--------------|
| Fleet server compromised | Attacker holds server key. Can cosign anything until key rotated. | Attacker operates within Guard constraints only. Module revoked by owners. No key to steal. |
| Single operator compromised | Depends on off-chain M-of-N quality. | On-chain threshold enforcement. Cannot act below threshold. Owner swapped atomically. |
| Server + 1 operator compromised | Potentially full control if M-of-N was bypassed | Server module limited to Tier 0/1 by Guard. Operator is 1 of N. Still below threshold. |
| Server database tampered | Audit trail lost | Audit trail on-chain. Immutable. Server logs are supplementary. |

