## 15. Known Limitations (v0.0.2)

1. **On-chain gas for Guard checks.** Guard validation adds gas cost to every
   Safe transaction. Optimized for low-frequency Tier 2/3 actions.
2. **Module-Guard latency.** On-chain execution adds ~2-5s latency for
   Tier 0/1 compared to pure off-chain cosigning in v0.0.1. Mitigated by
   caching policy decisions.
3. **Safe owner key security.** Safe inherits the security of its owners' key
   management. A compromised owner EOA is still a compromised signer.
4. **Single-fleet Safe.** Current design uses one Safe per fleet. Multi-fleet
   hierarchies (Safe of Safes) are possible but not specified.
5. **Oracle dependency for complex policy.** Geofencing and firmware
   attestation remain off-chain because on-chain oracles add cost and
   complexity.

